Public Api
Numex Exchange Pro provides HTTP APIs for interacting with the exchange public market data.
- Ticker
- Chart Data
- Volume

The HTTP API allows read access to public market data through the public endpoint -
- Public HTTP Endpoint: http://example.com/api/public

Ticker
Retrieves summary information for each currency/coin pair listed on the exchange.
- Ticker Endpoint: http://example.com/api/public?command=returnTicker

- Public HTTP Endpoint:
http://example.com/api/public?command=returnTicker&coinPair=DOGE_BTCChart Data
Returns candlestick chart data. Required GET parameters are "coinPair", "interval"
(candlestick interval in minutes; valid values are 5 = 5min, 15 = 15min, 30 = 30min, 120
= 2hr, 240 = 4hr, 1440 = 1 day). Fields include:


- Ticker Endpoint:
http://example.com/api/public?command=returnChartData&coinPair=DOGE_BTC&inter
val=1440
